out_desc_tool: The instrumentation used by the state of Texas to measure academic success is the Texas Assessment of Knowledge and Skills (TAKS) test. In 2003, the state introduced the TAKS test as the replacement for the previous version of the state of Texas assessment program called the Texas Assessment of Academic Skills. Texas, since the inception of the accountability system of standardized testing has assessed minimum basic skills in reading, writing, and mathematics.
